website_summaries.verdict: Combining advanced cooling technology with quality hardware, the Rosewill can give you greater control over your case temperature.
pros: With a microfin slim copper cooling block for better thermal conductivity, and a high-power pump at the radiator, rapid liquid circulation transfers heat quickly from your CPU
You'll also have more control over your fan and pump speed with this model's 4-pin pulse-width modulation
cons: May not be sufficient to overclock your machine, and the motherboard connection can be a bit unstable

customer_reviews.title: You get what you pay for.  Cheap and worthless!
customer_reviews.text: $16.00 for a CPU cooler that is worthless, cheap and easily cuts your flesh. Rosewill makes very good products. I just bought a mini-ATX case (Rosewill Micro-ATX Mini Tower Computer Case with Dual USB 3.0, Dual Fans and 12.5-Inch Card LINE-M Black) and it is perfect for the mission. Facts: The fins are cheap serrated and sharp aluminum, the heat pipes are in minimal contact with the CPU. The worst aspect is the retainer clips that are crimped on to the cheap aluminum block. It is impossible to attach with out cuts and bleeding. The fan is a joke. Sorry Rosewill, I am not impressed! Please do not purchase this item.
customer_reviews.author: Kevin McGuinness

customer_reviews.title: Bad experience
customer_reviews.text: I can only comment on my experience with this product as I have had plenty of Rosewill products with no issue. But this one should NOT have quiet in the name, sounded like a damn helicopter trying to take off, and that was on medium speed. The way the lines com off of radiator are kinda cheesy, they wont turn so you are relegated to installing it how the lines lay and that sometimes doesn't match your case design. I am disappointed in this one. Got a corsair in its place and I can barely hear it when its in performance mode, I mean day and night difference.
customer_reviews.author: Chris@Claire

customer_reviews.title: Good for the price but with caveats.
customer_reviews.text: So first of all, the unit came without its mounting mechanism nor its thermal compound, fortunately they agreed to send another unit, so that was 2 months to finally get a complete unit. So the cooler whole easy to mount it requires a lot of freaking pressure, so much you feel like you gonna break your board, but I guess that does work in its favor since the performance is surprisingly good for 10$, it cools my overclocked i7 just fine and its very quiet, so while the trouble is worth it, its a lot of trouble.
customer_reviews.author: Santiago

customer_reviews.title: Short life span.
customer_reviews.text: Block doesn't spread paste well. I've cleaned and remounted it a few times. The last test showed the pump isn't working anymore. The stock cooler I got with my CPU, a smaller Coolermaster is cooling it a lot better than this. Purchased in 2018 and didn't last 1 1/2 years. I used my PC for web browsing, streaming, Office files work, and other minor tasks. No high stress activity that would cause higher temperatures. You get what you pay for, Skip this and invest in a better AIO if you're going to water cool your CPU.
customer_reviews.author: B. Mason

customer_reviews.title: Temps brought down 15C
customer_reviews.text: it was ez to install you will not cut your fingers . I used the supplied cpu paste and lowered my temps 10C-15C Using system sandra complete cpu benchmark the cpu temp would reach 84C after using this cooler those temps were 72C . This bench Mark stresses your cpu you will not be able to put these kind of stresses on your cpu in real life. Heavy gaming the cpu reached 58C down from 70C . Asrock Z390 I5-9400F PC3000 @ 3200 GTX 960
customer_reviews.author: Wildcatt

customer_reviews.title: Don't bother, keep looking.
customer_reviews.text: Completely useless. Attempted to attach the cooler to the motherboard using the supplied AMD hooks and that was a no go. The way the hooks are integrated into the base of the cooler won't allow you to even reach the retention brackets for the motherboard. I tried hooking one side and then the other... the first hook from the cooler actually snapped off of it with next to no force from me. So now I've got a CPU cooler with a coat of thermal paste on it and broken bracket. Best waste of $25 I've had in a while. Don't waste your time, especially if you are using the supplied AMD hooks.
customer_reviews.author: Zack

customer_reviews.title: Very quiet and cool!
customer_reviews.text: I was very pleasantly surprised by this CPU cooler. I am using this on a 3.0 GHz Core 2 Quad processor and bought it only because I needed a cooler easy to install for quick bench checks on motherboards. I have a couple of the tall radiator type coolers which are difficult to install/remove and many times will not fit due to interfering with adjacent parts. This cooler not only fits anywhere and installs in a snap, but seems to keep things as cool as these larger more expensive units.
customer_reviews.author: Jacob

customer_reviews.title: Quiet and keeps everything nice and cool!
customer_reviews.text: Was a little tight getting it into my wife's computer as it is a little big. It took me some time to get it situated and all the wires routed around it because there wasn't a lot of room for my hands in there. Once in place and turned on her computer worked like a charm and runs nice and quiet. I will order another one for my computer next time I upgrade it.
customer_reviews.author: Mickey

customer_reviews.title: Great Cooler!
customer_reviews.text: Great cooler, installs easily if you're uncertain about the Intel plastic brackets just search YouTube for a guide video. This cooler is about twice the size of the stock Intel cooler but is still nice and compact in my Phanteks Enthoo Evolv ITX case. I bought this for the second hand Intel i7-4770K I just got and it's working like a charm keeping it cool. I'm not overclocking so the CPU is at 3.5Ghz. It comes with the thermal paste pre-applied Hope this helps.
customer_reviews.author: Kereltis

customer_reviews.title: Purchased this for my nephew's first build
customer_reviews.text: I picked this up for my nephew as he had made a list for a new computer build. He ultimately left cooling system off of his list... So a little thermal paste and this bad-boy and he was able to complete his system that day.. So far, everything looks pretty good from a cooling perspective. Obviously his fan setup and case have a significant play in this, but it looks really good so far.
customer_reviews.author: David C. Brock Jr

customer_reviews.title: Not bad at all! Great value!!
customer_reviews.text: Needed something cheap with just a bit of bling to enhance an older i5-750 powered PC I am selling and this fit the bill! Overclocked the processor and it kept tempretures well within safe levels under full load without being too loud! I will be purchasing this again for my next computer Flip/build!!! The mounting bracket is kind of cheap feeling and the instructions didn't really go in to detale....otherwise Great!!
customer_reviews.author: Zombierot

customer_reviews.title: Nothing works as advertised
customer_reviews.text: The remote controller that came with this does not work and all my fans run much slower when plugged into the fan hub that came with this. The fact that I have an rgb setup that I can't control the LEDs on is disappointing. Doubly so as both this and the case I bought are advertised aura sync compatible but don't work with the rgb header on my Asus motherboard so I also can't control anything from the software side.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Noisier than advertised
customer_reviews.text: Even with the Asus system fan utility set to "Silent" the fan still generates about 35db with a 35W processor and minimal load on the system. And the noise is very high pitched, it's like having a mosquito buzzing in your ear non-stop. I had a headache and ringing ears from being around the computer for about 1/2 hour. This system has already had other problems and now has to sit another few days until the Noctua I ordered gets here...
customer_reviews.author: Bill O.

customer_reviews.title: Great value - my go-to CPU cooler
customer_reviews.text: This is my second time using this cooler in a budget gaming build. Overall, it's a simple but effective cooler. I have used it with both a i5-2500K and a i7-4790K. The i5 was overclocked to 4.3, and idle temps stayed in the high 20s, and never went above high 50s at peak load. The i7 is stock speed and idles in the low 30s and peaks in the low 60s. This cooler is quiet - much quieter than the stock Intel fan. And it looks great with one of the many gaming motherboards that have red accents. Highly recommended - great value for the price.
customer_reviews.author: carolina.country

customer_reviews.title: overall i rated this a 3 star for amd clip issue
customer_reviews.text: overall it got to me in perfect condition. the only big issue i am having is the clamp for the amd. seeing one i have is so crimp up that am having to bend it back to a normal highest like most amd socket clips . so just a heads up on that everyone. i do wise the manf fixes this issue. also this will work for lower power cpu. fx lvl and above will have cooling issues
customer_reviews.author: A. Gulla

customer_reviews.title: Great for replacing stock cooler, not otherwise!
customer_reviews.text: Buyer beware, if you do NOT have the stock motherboard backplate installed or available to put back on, this will NOT work. I have an AM3+ socket and had an AIO water cooler that the pump went out on. I decided to replace with an easy solution, this was not the case. Rosewill is a brand which I've trusted and will continue to use, but this particular product is not a good aftermarket aftermarket replacement, if that makes sense. If I were upgrading from stock to this, it would probably be an entirely different review.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Great value, great product
customer_reviews.text: Heatsink is above average quality, fan is virtually silent. Fins are slightly thinner than more expensive products, making the unit feel a little bit lightweight. Using with i5 3570k at 4.2 GHz in a room at 70F. Prime 95 temps with stock Heatsink/Fan after 10 seconds = 90C. (Temps seemed as though they would creep even higher- stopped after 20 seconds) Prime 95 temps with RCX-ZAIO-92 after 1 hour = 70C Idle temperatures identical with stock, @35C. Dropped temps 20C on a moderate overclock with a $14.99 product. Outstanding value. There are certainly better products out there for 3 times the price, but the law of diminishing returns will be severely evident. Highly recommended for moderate air-cooled overclocking.
customer_reviews.author: Misfit

customer_reviews.title: Possibly a Problem Long-Term
customer_reviews.text: The Packaging was good and included some thermal paste/grease which I didn't use. the mounting mechanism is somewhat questionable and I was mounting to a lga 1155 motherboard. at first, I thought it wouldn't be able to mount due to the sheer force it would put on the CPU but I got it locked in place with both latches and everything works fine. the brace uses a 2-pin system which is very easy to install. the fan pushes enough air to keep an i5 3350p around 35-45 degrees Celcius. Overall decent quality but it is a very cheap fins on the heatsink. In the end, I would recommend for old OEM systems or anyone on a budget
customer_reviews.author: Caleb Dela Cruz

customer_reviews.title: Mounting standoff scratched my motherboard and killed half of my RAM slots.
customer_reviews.text: The hard plastic standoffs for mounting the cooler block scratched my motherboard when I tightened it up. Computer kept rebooting and could never get to the OS. Took out the Ram sticks furthest from the processor and it would boot. I am stuck with half the amount of RAM I wanted to usebecause of this POS cooler.
customer_reviews.author: Glen Roberts

customer_reviews.title: Sometimes aftermarket doesn't work
customer_reviews.text: I honestly have no idea if the product works or not! Why not? The mounting apparatus is push pins, not screws. I can't mount the thing! It would have been the perfect solution to my cooling problems, but if I can't get it to mount to the board, what's the point? I'm extremely disappointed. My computer will now have to be modified? I don't think so. I'll find another company to fix the issue.
customer_reviews.author: Sheri G.

customer_reviews.title: Great deal (for me)
customer_reviews.text: Didn't have any leaks. Temps are pretty darn good. Mounting was somewhat troublesome, but after doing it once I could comfortably do it in a fraction of the time next time. I'd definitely recommend it for the $24 I paid.
customer_reviews.author: S. Gemboski

customer_reviews.title: Super easy to install and better than stock cpu fan
customer_reviews.text: We built a linux-based HTPC for the kids' hang out space. Rather than use the larger noisier fan that came with the CPU, I followed the advice of a website and tried this cooler. It's super quiet, and keeps the CPU core temp lower than the published specs for the stock fan.
customer_reviews.author: Damien Daurio

customer_reviews.title: slight noise at first but great value option
customer_reviews.text: seemed to make a few ever so slight gurgling noises after first install but i haven't noticed a thing since. my i5 9600k over clocks to 5 ghz easy now and the temps are very nice. looks very stylish in my black and white build and fit perfectly in my snowblind element.
customer_reviews.author: Dokken

customer_reviews.title: Works very well.
customer_reviews.text: Works great. The idle temps are about 5-8 degrees higher than a better quality CPU Fan/HS cooler (in the $30+ range), but the max temps with Prime95 running for hours is only about 3-5 degrees higher than the good CPU Fan/HS coolers. BTW, I sell processors on eBay and I have tested over 500+ Core 2 Quad / 771 Xeon processors on this puppy and other higher end model CPU Fan/HS units. The only con is after awhile, the bottom clips may break. It's due to the poor Intel stock fan style design.
customer_reviews.author: Wanos

customer_reviews.title: 10 degrees worse than stock cooler. Tower cooler with blue fan.
customer_reviews.text: POS. This is for the blue fan tower cooler. Worse temps than stock cooler in i7-8700 non k. I just wanted a little better than stock. This thing sucked! 10 degrees worse. P.S. Stop lumping products together so we know about the 1 product being reviewed!
customer_reviews.author: Jedakiah Roper

customer_reviews.title: Rosewill RCX-Z1 - Silent
customer_reviews.text: This review is for the Rosewill RCX-Z1 fan, installed on a 95 watt AMD socket AM3 cpu. It's been installed for just about two weeks now and so far so good. Both the fan and heat sink are larger than the stock AMD unit, the fan is absolutely 100% dead silent.
customer_reviews.author: -BFS

customer_reviews.title: Direct Factory Replacement
customer_reviews.text: Look closely, the fan has a Z. This is a Zalman cooler repackaged by Rosewill, and offered at a lower cost. If you need to replace the Intel factory cooler, this is a direct replacement. It's hard to say how well this compares to the factory cooler. I had to pull it to remove the hard drive, and the plastic pins were bent out to the point I could not properly remount it. This plugged right in and worked perfect. Temps under full load with Prime95 Max Heat never exceeded 78 degrees.
customer_reviews.author: Irwin Electronics

customer_reviews.title: Great price for a good cooler
customer_reviews.text: Great price for a good cooler, Cools my Intel Core 2 Quad Q9300 at full load and temps don't go over 60 C,Works great, and quiet. Awesome looking red and black fan. Copper core. Very quiet. Easy to install. Compact, does not require a lot of extra space around the CPU socket to mount. - Thermal compound already applied for a perfect fit! - Performance is better than an OEM Intel heatsink & fan - Great value for the money - Great performance - Even comes with decent installation instructions
customer_reviews.author: Carlos Chamorro Schutze

customer_reviews.title: plastic snap in screws don't fit all 775 socket motherboards
customer_reviews.text: plastic snap in screws don't fit all 775 motherboards, they should include the metal screws as a backup , I was able to use screws from my old heatsink with some plastic washers added to get it to mount, the fan and heatsink actually work good for basic pcs but I recommend staying away from this one and going with a cooler master for the extra buck, don't take the risk of it not fitting your mobo
customer_reviews.author: Cosmic Southwest

customer_reviews.title: so quiet don't hear it
customer_reviews.text: fan/cooling unit used as replacement in an HP Slim Desktop that was placed in service 7/17/17. Square Trade said it wasn't economical to repair?!?!?! $12 >< for fan/cooling unit + time for my grandson to replace.
customer_reviews.author: R H Brenneman Sr

customer_reviews.title: Pretty awful
customer_reviews.text: Product was defective on arrival. No clear or concise instructions on how to install am4 mounting kit and was leaking and tubing was loose on arrival. Still waiting on my refund. Rosewill is putting me through an rma process for this shitty 40 dollar cooler. Save yourself the hassle and get something better. Saving an extra 20 bucks was not worth it for me
customer_reviews.author: MATTHEW J KLUNIS

customer_reviews.title: Sturdy fan for the intel processor.
customer_reviews.text: I wanted a new fan for new processor (used) that will replace the old processor (failing). So far after a couple of weeks, this fan is working great with the new processor (used). It feels good to bring life back (save money) to an older computer.
customer_reviews.author: Glen P.

customer_reviews.title: Good for the price
customer_reviews.text: It's not too loud but you definitely can hear it when it quiet, performs well, i5 9400f @4ghz idle is 22c and gaming is 50-60c I just wish the tubes were a bit longer, I had to mount the waterblock upside down cuz it wasn't long enough
customer_reviews.author: Shawn

customer_reviews.title: Works great! A little tricky to get on
customer_reviews.text: Okay, mounting system is tricky. It’s definitely secure but tricky and I felt like I was going to break something getting it on. But once you do it you’ll get the hang of it. It’s quiet and looks very nice. Did I mention it works great?
customer_reviews.author: jonah

customer_reviews.title: Great for replacing a broken or missing stock cooler (not a suitable alternative).
customer_reviews.text: Good CPU cooler if your stock cooler has broke and you just want the cheapest thing that can replace it. I definitely don't see myself buying this thing as a suitable replacement for the stock cooler. I actually only bought it because my old Q9550 LGA775 Intel CPU didn't come with a stock cooler. It works great for an HTPC case that isn't going to be overclocked. I would, however, recommend that Noctua's low profile CPU coolers be considered before purchasing this cooler as an after market replacement.
customer_reviews.author: John

customer_reviews.title: Stay away from these types of fans
customer_reviews.text: The plastic pins that insert into the motherboard are fragile and break if forced in (and they don't always go in even after jiggling them around), this item included. Go for a fan that uses another type of connector.
customer_reviews.author: Lee

customer_reviews.title: Tiny yet impressive.
customer_reviews.text: This thing is tiny. Currently cooling a 1600x and it stays on a cool 70 under max load, then again my home is kinda chilly at 70 degrees.
customer_reviews.author: Jose Vargas

customer_reviews.title: Five Stars
customer_reviews.text: Just installed it and so far working good,. but after just over 2 years now the power supply went bad again. I have to remove the CPU fan to get the old power supply out and install the new PSU and when I did, 3 out of 4 plastic clips holding the CPU fan on broke. They were very brittle from the heat I guess but the fan on the CPU was lose when I went to remove it. Now I don't know if the fan came lose and caused it to heat up and make them brittle or if they just do that over time. I don't know. I'm not judging.
customer_reviews.author: Clifford J Serene

customer_reviews.title: Keeps my frankenbuild cool
customer_reviews.text: Took a business motherboard with a noisy fan, put it in a bigger case and used this cooler. Nice low temperatures.
customer_reviews.author: Bud K

customer_reviews.title: Installation issues with old motherboard.
customer_reviews.text: I could not get it installed. The plastic clips will not snap down into my lga1156 motherboard. It is made for screws. I was using enough pressure in trying to get them installed that I was worried about damaging my motherboard.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Great Thermal Performance
customer_reviews.text: I have tried a few of these type heat sinks. This one here with its copper base soaked up the heat far better than the other typical all aluminum ones I have tried.
customer_reviews.author: seulater

customer_reviews.title: Cool so far.
customer_reviews.text: Ordered this on Friday and received on Saturday. It has only been running around 10 hours now, This is a really quiet fan and my computer is running great again. Took under a minute to install as I had my processor clean and ready for this new heat sink and fan. I like the fact it is pre-pasted and ready to go straight out of the box. I will update if needed but for now I give it five stars.
customer_reviews.author: gutterbanger

customer_reviews.title: Met my exact needs
customer_reviews.text: My old fan broke while upgrading my cpu. This fan was an exact replacement. It operates soundlessly.
customer_reviews.author: BikeMore

customer_reviews.title: Overheated my computer
customer_reviews.text: Crap cooler. When I received it and installed it it make my computer overheat multiple times. I had to return it and put my old cooler back in. I only had a I5-7400
customer_reviews.author: Carlos

customer_reviews.title: While this cooler did fine at stock settings and light overclocking
customer_reviews.text: This unit worked well for me, at first. Not long after installing it, I began to overclock and so how far I could push my CPU (4690k). While this cooler did fine at stock settings and light overclocking, it couldn't keep up when I started to push. I had to keep my OC pretty low until I was able to replace the cooler. Still, it was not my expectation for this to be a big overclocking cooler. It did what I expected it to do and I am satisfied with the value for what I paid for it.
customer_reviews.author: Erin

customer_reviews.title: For what it is, it works. But I don't think it even had a PCM.
customer_reviews.text: For what it is, it works. But I don't think it even had a PCM. Not the best out there.
customer_reviews.author: bobby3h

customer_reviews.title: Great fan but a bit difficult to install
customer_reviews.text: the fan was a bit difficult to install because I had to push the clips really hard so I was afraid to damage my cpu. I used this fan on an Intel and AMD cpu.
customer_reviews.author: Miguel Espinoza

customer_reviews.title: Works as advertised
customer_reviews.text: I purchased this product to replace a dying factory fan. It works exactly as advertised although the mounting hardware is pretty chintzy. The computer would randomly shut off a few seconds after start and I was having trouble diagnosing the problem. I tried getting into the BIOS thinking it was a software issue. After a few minutes of no luck I reluctantly opened the case to see what hardware had skit the bed. Turns out the fan was hanging off the CPU only being held in by 2 of the 4 studs. Make sure not to move your case around too much or it will work loose like mine did.
customer_reviews.author: Ekim

customer_reviews.title: Virtually the same specs as some CPU fans that cost ...
customer_reviews.text: Virtually the same specs as some CPU fans that cost more than $100. If this is compatible with your CPU, and you do not have special cooling needs--and if you do, consider liquid cooling--buy this.
customer_reviews.author: Thomas F Gross

customer_reviews.title: WORKS AMAZINGLY
customer_reviews.text: Easy install.....keeps cpu cool and was so economical. Great product. Extremely happy with it.
customer_reviews.author: Nicholas Ansbro

customer_reviews.title: RCX-Z300 great LGA775 cooler
customer_reviews.text: I'm very pleased with this. It clips into place much easier than the OEM Intel coolers and also seems to do a better job.
customer_reviews.author: JW Wimpy

customer_reviews.title: It DOES fit intel socket 1155
customer_reviews.text: Used this to replace the stock cooler in my wife's PC. I will verify for the people doubting what socket it will fit that it is definitely compatible with socket 1155. It works as expected, and is a decent improvement over the intel stock cooler, which is fine since my wife doesn't use the pc for heavy gaming.
customer_reviews.author: dragonfyre79

customer_reviews.title: Great addition for an AMD Phenom CPU
customer_reviews.text: Fit perfectly to my AMD Phenom II X4 CPU. The pins holding it to the board were VERY hard to get locked into place, mainly due to a combination of their design and the board space allocated. Once you do get it locked in, it works as expected. The fan is also extremely quiet (if you're not near the PC, it's not easily detectable).
customer_reviews.author: einsteinxx

customer_reviews.title: Simple, effective, easy to install
customer_reviews.text: This is one of the best basic use heat-sinks out there. The slim profile allows it to fit in almost any case and allows for easy install. Been running it in a media center PC for about 6 months. Pros: Easy to install Quiet - using it in my media PC Reliable FAN Solid construction Ultra low profile for small cases Efficient air flow Cons: None!
customer_reviews.author: Nick Glazer

customer_reviews.title: Great Fan. Quiet and Efficient.
customer_reviews.text: This is the second RCX-Z300 that I've purchased. The first one lasted a long time, but when the fan ultimately died, I decided to replace it with a different unit. That was a mistake... I left the other one on for a while, but it was loud, and didn't seem to do a very good job keeping my processor cool. As a result I put another one of these in, and it works great!
customer_reviews.author: Wes

customer_reviews.title: Good fan for the money
customer_reviews.text: This fan does it's job. It's not as quiet as a 120mm fan, but a lot quieter than a stock CPU cooler. The thermal paste it comes with is okay if you aren't overclocking. If you overclock I would recommend a better paste and probably better cooler. It keeps my CPU anywhere between 3-8c cooler under load. I really only got this because the CPU cooler was loud. It loses a star because the AMD bracket was flimsy garbage. It was a pain to mount.
customer_reviews.author: Ann-Marie

customer_reviews.title: fine fan for the price
customer_reviews.text: installed ok, works well enough. I'd advise adding an little dab of thermal paste. the skim layer it ships with is pretty light.
customer_reviews.author: s.deornellas

customer_reviews.title: It is fairly tall. Make sure you have plenty of clearance.
customer_reviews.text: Works great. I installed it within 15 minutes of getting it. A little hard to lock it onto its mounting ring, but at least I know it is nice and tight to the cpu. The height was an issue in my case due to my large side fan on my case, but I made it work.
customer_reviews.author: Mike

customer_reviews.title: This should be the stock Intel CPU cooler!!!
customer_reviews.text: So shocked by the shear value of this little heatsink. For only around $10-12, it's super quiet especially during boot up. It can get a little noisier during gaming but that's a given unless you go liquid cooling. As my title says, I believe this little bad boy should be the stock Intel CPU cooler, I doubt there's much of a big difference in quality control but Rosewill shows how well this performs for an inexpensive alternative. I would recommend it especially due to the black and red theme it has on the 92mm fan and shroud.
customer_reviews.author: Steven Long

customer_reviews.title: Could Not Figure Out How to Attach It!
customer_reviews.text: I could not connect it to my CPU! and it had no directions explaining what I was doing wrong, if anything. The pressure it was putting on my CPU wile trying to lock it down was terrifying. Thankfully one of its connectors broke and I threw the whole thing in the trash and ordered an Intel CPU cooler which installed intuitively.
customer_reviews.author: Jim Stein

customer_reviews.title: Quiet and cheap.
customer_reviews.text: I like the famous Cooler Master hyper 212, but this is a solid pick at half the price. I had a new build, and when I went to put the back plate on, there was a chip in the way, so I put this on, and it is doing an excellent job of quietly cooling my Intel G2020. Admittedly, a low power CPU, but it is currently running at 800 rpm, 47 C as I stress test it.
customer_reviews.author: drh3b

customer_reviews.title: Better than a stock cooler!
customer_reviews.text: The cooler works much better than a stock cooler. Works exactly as advertised.
customer_reviews.author: Phoenix

customer_reviews.title: Good CPU Heatsink / Fan for the price.
customer_reviews.text: These are pretty good, especially for the price. They are much easier to install, even if you remove it, and re-install this item it works much better that the standard ones provided with Intel processors. If you use a good paste like Arctic Silver,etc. They work fine if you run a computer at or near stock settings. I used one on a Core 2 Duo E8600, and another one on a Core 2 Quad 9650.
customer_reviews.author: Gregory M. Spitzer

customer_reviews.title: Perfect for a Mini-ITX build
customer_reviews.text: I was in the midst of putting together a small form factor desktop for a friend when I realized the cooler that came with the CPU would not fit with the power-supply in the case he selected. This product was the solution! It fit underneath the PS with room to spare and keeps the CPU nice and cool. My one word of warning is that this particular item comes pre-greased with thermal compound and this fact isn't mentioned on the packaging, so save yourself a mess and handle with care.
customer_reviews.author: GROWE

customer_reviews.title: Good at it's job
customer_reviews.text: But louder than I expected. I've got in on an old duo-core that runs fairly hot (photo processing mainly) and this dropped the temps from the mid 50°C range into the upper 40°C range and sped Ol' Sparky up a bit. But it is noticeably louder than the 80mm stock unit that it replaced. If I moved the computer under the desk rather than right on top, I doubt I'd hear it at all, but the machine sits right next to me.
customer_reviews.author: Bassnote

customer_reviews.title: Fantastic cooler minus all the complicated brackets common with other ...

customer_reviews.title: Works fairly good.
customer_reviews.text: The unit works good, for those having noise issues check to make sure your motherboard's fan control is working, they tend to stop working with bigger fans and run them full speed. For the money this is a good product.

customer_reviews.title: A functional and cost-effective replacement for the OEM unit
customer_reviews.text: The stock cooler on my Intel i7-920 with LGA 1366 socket had finally given up after seven years' long service. I had a project due, and I needed a new cooler for a low price, tomorrow, to keep my computer running. I specifically was looking for a cooler that used push pins so I could swap coolers easily and quickly without removing my computer's motherboard. This unit is affordable, quiet, easy to install, and works much than the OEM unit ever did. I recommend it to anyone who needs a CPU cooler, especially if they are pressed for time. Combine with Arctic Silver MX4 for best results.

customer_reviews.text: This fan turned out to be exactly what I needed. I was building a PC using a Mini-Box M350 Mini-ITX case. Only ID-Cooling IS-20i comes close to this cooler as far as quality/price ratio.
customer_reviews.author: Fabián Gómez

However it is not that quiet. Do not expect silent at all. Go for a Zalman or another brand of something if you want a really quiet PC. Will be returning.

customer_reviews.title: works great !!
customer_reviews.text: I got this when i updated/replaced a bad motherboard in an old HP for my daughter. It is cooling an old AMD 64 X2 4400 CPU. On a $50 N68C-GS ASrock mobo with 4G of Corsair ddr2 ram. I have it overclocked to 3.1Ghz from a stock 2.3Ghz and it has never been over 46C* yet with this cooling unit. A little noisy at full speed, but not too bad. It does it's job well.

product_meta.title: Rosewill CPU Liquid Cooler, Closed Loop PC Water Cooling, Quiet 120mm PWM Fan, Intel LGA 2011/2066/1366/1150/1151/1155/1156/775, AMD AM4/AM3+/AM3/AM2+/AM2/AM1/FM2+/FM1 - PB120
feature_bullets: CPU Water Cooler: Transfer heat away from your CPU and GPU more quickly than air with this water-based coolant method of cooling, featuring low-evaporation tubes to keep coolant from drying up too quickly.

CLOSED LOOP COOLER: This self-contained cooling system, closed loop design with pre-filled coolant is virtually immune to leaks with no refill needed, even with rapid liquid circulation from the built-in high power water pump on radiator.
PWM FAN SPEED CONTROL: One 120mm fan with 4-pin pulse-width modulation allows you to ramp up or lower your fan and pump speed, giving you more control
EASY INSTALLATION: Effortlessly upgrade your stock CPU fan to the efficiency of Intel/AMD compatible liquid CPU cooling in a few easy steps
PERFORMANCE COPPER BASE: Equipped with a microfin, slim copper cold plate cooling block for better thermal conductivity, effective heat transfer and low noise
